The Great Samsara was an ancient Tretmolec of Royal blood. Her Father and Brother were both killed by the Varanas when she was a girl, but the spirit within her gave her strength to move on. Samsara had power in her eyes, but until she left the Tretmolec village after the comming of the Atmah Cyane, she did not realise that the power came from her Mother, The Great Gaia herself.<br>
After she left her Amazon village, she was captured by lizard like people calling themselves Saurians. She was taken to their king who himself was a human but unlike the Varanas she had met and killed before. He was kind and a good man. His name was Ktor. Samsara and Ktor were married under Saurian law and she soon gave birth to a daughter whom she named Karina. <br>
Years later, Karina brought a young man to the Kingdom who turned out to be the son of Kor, of the Varanas. Samsara ordered that Karina never see him again, but Ktor took pity on the boy which caused a large fight between the King and Queen of the Saurians. Karina left with Kinar, son of Kor, and he led her back to the Tretmolec village where his people, along with Saurian allies who had conspired against their king, and they slaughtered the Amazon village.<br>
Samsara knew her daughter was in danger and she left her home in search of her old village. When she arrived she was mistaken that Karina had already been killed. So while she followed Cyane into a hut that was on fire, the Varanas attacked and killed both Amazon Queens. Meanwhile, Karina watched in horror as her mother and village died. Then the Saurians turned on the Varanas killing every last one of them. As they tossed Karina into the pit to devour her, a large white wolf came forth defending the princess. Sadly, both were eventually killed. Ktor was led to believe that Samsara betrayed him, and even in his last moments of life, he declared his hatred for the Tretmolec kind.<br>
<br>
Centuries later, the Atmah Cyane came to a woman called Meg Leandros. She told Meg that her daughter Sayler would soon birth the next Amazon Queen of the Nation and she must protect her for in her, the Nation would be changed for the better. When Sayler gave birth to a baby girl naming her Alysia Lillian Loire, Meg told her that she was the reincarnation of the Goddess Kimbia, an evil darkness that must not leave the amazons protection. While Sayler stayed in Rome with friends, Alysia was raised by Queen Ariah of Ephesus and Queen Genesis Tiberon. She was taught how to fight and healer as well. When she was eleven years old, the village was attacked by a fleet of Romans, where Alysia murdered a Roman general to save her Queen from being killed. After her first kill, she wanted more. She saught out assasins lurking in the woods surrounding Ephesus, and killed them all. Upon her amazon initiation, she was given a sword by Velasca, and the blessing of strength surpassing any man. By Artemis she was given a crossbow, and blessed arrows that only Alysia could remove. And from Athena, she was given the title of &quot;Amazon Goddess of Healing.&quot;<br>
