She found little in her life left, so she ventured to Rome to find her Mother. On the way, she met another man named Hercules. His kindness drew her in and sure enough, a child was born. In honor of the love of her first daughter, she called this one Cora Alena Loire. Hercules soon left fearing that Hera would find the girl and kill her. Cora was blessed by the Gods calling her a &quot;Messanger&quot; of the Fates. The Fates came to Aly, telling her to leave Ephesus and go to Rome,for Cora's future was there. She did as was told after the Gods threatened her village.<br>
In Rome she met a woman named Livia and soon fell in love with her. She became Livia's champion and rode with her into battle against many enemies. However, Livia never told Aly of the murders against Amazons and Elisians. <br>
During this time in Alysia's life, the Ancients of the Tretmolecs were conspiring. See, Karina was supposed to be reborn to Samsara, but the Gods interviened and Cora was born instead. Karina was reborn to an amazon named Anya in Rome.<br>
Anya was killed and the baby girl was found by Livia and her Champion Alysia. They took the girl in and raised her as their own naming her Isabella Veronica Krapurs. A Roman name.<br>
After Xena came and took Livia away, Alysia traveled off to find her. Sadly, she returned to Rome without Livia and was told by her army that Rome was attacked and Isabella was killed.<br>
She left Rome in search of her amazon home, but when they saw the mark of Livia on her leathers, she was turned away. Queen Hippolyte of Themiscrya took Alysia in and soon Aly was raised up an amazon once more. She never got over the loss of Livia and Isabella, and buried her anger into drinking. One night at the local tavern, she drank too much and ended up pregnant by a man calling himself Iolaus.<br>
He was called off to war and she was called to Delphi where she was told by the Oracle that her new child would become the next Oracle of Delphi.<br>
Alysia remained in Themiscrya for her pregnancy but Cora was still in Rome and she missed her daughter. She went into labor in the Roman palace, and gave birth to the next Oracle of Delphi, naming her Aliya Gabrielle Loire.<br>
However, there was another. Aliya had a twin sister. Alysia named her, Alexa Xena Loire.<br>
Alysia returned to Themiscrya and trained her girls there as well as in Ephesus where she was welcomed back. The girls were both developing powers, and were aged quickly to assist in their development. Aliya became more of a peacemaker, and Alexa a warrior and inventor. Sadly, because of Alysia's selfishness, she lost connection between herself and Alexa. <br>
Aliya remained in Ephesus, as well as Delphi and Rome. The Goddess Artemis then impregnated Aliya with a child who was named Melody Nicola Loire, Roman Goddess of Music.<br>
Cora too, was wed to a man named Alastor Alcon. Cora in turn gave birth to a boy naming him, Julian Alastor Alcon. Alysia and Alastor never got along, and both knew it well.<br>
During the same time as Julain was born, Alysia gave birth to a boy who she called, Wulf Heracles Loire.<br>
Wulf was killed early on in life and through Dawnithinia Rivent Darkshade's daughter, he was brought back to life thus becomming Alysia and Dawn's son.<br>
After Wulf was born, Cora gave birth to a little girl naming her Odessa Sayler Alcon.<br>
Alysia herself raised the girl in Scynthia, where Alysia was Amazon Queen.<br>
Alysia eventually met a man of the Elisians, his name was Eli. She was married to him and gave birth to a girl naming her Vyiana Cyane Loire. A dark power erased most memory of Eli and Vyi from her mind, and Alysia retreated back to Scynthia.<br>
